# Wireless System Simulation and Validation

This repository contains MATLAB and Python-based wireless system simulation and validation projects focused on RF/PHY performance evaluation, radio-link analysis, RF impairments, beamforming behavior, OTA/MPAC concepts, PA nonlinearity, DPD validation, and 5G/NTN wireless-system modeling.

The goal of this repository is to demonstrate practical engineering capability in simulation-driven validation: not only generating results, but also defining assumptions, implementing models, comparing performance metrics, analyzing trade-offs, and validating wireless-system behavior using reproducible MATLAB and Python workflows.

---

## Repository Scope

This repository focuses on simulation and validation topics related to:

* RF link budget and coverage analysis
* Path loss, shadowing, and fading-channel modeling
* 5G NR TDD frame and resource-grid simulation
* RF impairments such as EVM, ACLR, phase noise, and IQ imbalance
* Power amplifier nonlinearity and DPD validation
* Beam sweeping and beam-selection behavior
* OTA/MPAC quiet-zone and chamber-validation concepts
* NTN Doppler, delay, and link-budget validation
* Monte Carlo-based wireless performance analysis

---

## Repository Structure

```text
wireless-system-simulation-validation/
│
├── 01_rf_link_budget_and_coverage_validation/
├── 02_5g_nr_tdd_frame_and_resource_grid_simulation/
├── 03_path_loss_shadowing_and_fading_channel_analysis/
├── 04_rf_impairments_evm_aclr_validation/
├── 05_phase_noise_and_iq_imbalance_simulation/
├── 06_pa_nonlinearity_and_dpd_validation/
├── 07_beam_sweeping_and_beam_selection_simulation/
├── 08_ota_mpac_quiet_zone_validation/
├── 09_ntn_doppler_delay_and_link_validation/
└── 10_monte_carlo_wireless_performance_analysis/
```

Each project folder follows a consistent structure:

```text
project_folder/
│
├── matlab/        # MATLAB simulation scripts
├── python/        # Python simulation scripts
├── results/       # Generated numerical results
├── figures/       # Plots and visualization outputs
├── docs/          # Technical notes, equations, and analysis
└── README.md      # Project-specific explanation
```

---

## Projects

### 01. RF Link Budget and Coverage Validation

This project validates wireless link-budget behavior by estimating received power, path loss, noise floor, SNR/SINR, receiver sensitivity, and coverage range under different deployment assumptions.

Key topics:

* Free-space path loss
* Log-distance path loss
* Receiver noise floor
* Link margin
* Coverage-radius estimation
* Uplink/downlink budget comparison

Typical outputs:

* Received power vs distance
* SNR vs distance
* Coverage threshold analysis
* Link-margin comparison

---

### 02. 5G NR TDD Frame and Resource Grid Simulation

This project models basic 5G NR time-frequency resource structures and validates how numerology, subcarrier spacing, slot duration, bandwidth, and TDD patterns affect resource availability.

Key topics:

* 5G NR numerology
* Subcarrier spacing
* OFDM symbol structure
* Slot duration
* TDD DL/UL pattern
* Resource-grid visualization

Typical outputs:

* Time-frequency resource grid
* DL/UL symbol allocation
* Slot-level resource usage
* Numerology comparison

---

### 03. Path Loss, Shadowing, and Fading Channel Analysis

This project analyzes wireless propagation behavior using deterministic and statistical channel models. It compares path loss, log-normal shadowing, Rayleigh fading, and Rician fading effects on received signal quality.

Key topics:

* Large-scale path loss
* Log-normal shadowing
* Rayleigh fading
* Rician fading
* Channel gain distribution
* Outage probability

Typical outputs:

* Path loss vs distance
* Received power distribution
* Fading envelope plots
* Outage probability curves

---

### 04. RF Impairments, EVM, and ACLR Validation

This project validates the impact of RF impairments on signal quality using EVM and spectral-regrowth metrics. It studies how transmitter impairments degrade modulation accuracy and adjacent-channel performance.

Key topics:

* Error Vector Magnitude, EVM
* Adjacent Channel Leakage Ratio, ACLR
* Additive noise
* Gain imbalance
* Phase imbalance
* Carrier leakage
* Spectral regrowth

Typical outputs:

* Constellation diagrams
* EVM vs SNR
* Power spectral density
* ACLR comparison
* Impairment sensitivity analysis

---

### 05. Phase Noise and IQ Imbalance Simulation

This project models phase noise and IQ imbalance effects in RF transceiver chains and validates their impact on constellation quality, EVM, and spectrum.

Key topics:

* Oscillator phase noise
* Common phase error
* IQ gain imbalance
* IQ phase mismatch
* Image rejection ratio
* Receiver impairment modeling

Typical outputs:

* Impaired constellation plots
* EVM degradation curves
* Spectrum with image components
* Phase-noise sensitivity results

---

### 06. PA Nonlinearity and DPD Validation

This project models power amplifier nonlinearity and validates digital predistortion concepts for improving transmitter linearity.

Key topics:

* Power amplifier AM-AM distortion
* Power amplifier AM-PM distortion
* Rapp model
* Saleh model
* Memory polynomial model
* Digital predistortion
* EVM and ACLR improvement

Typical outputs:

* AM-AM curve
* AM-PM curve
* Input/output spectrum
* ACLR before and after DPD
* EVM before and after DPD

---

### 07. Beam Sweeping and Beam Selection Simulation

This project simulates beam sweeping and beam selection for directional wireless links. It validates how beam direction, angular resolution, antenna gain, and channel direction affect received signal quality.

Key topics:

* Beam sweeping
* Beam selection
* Array response
* Directional gain
* Beam misalignment
* SNR-based beam decision

Typical outputs:

* Beam pattern plots
* Received power per beam
* Best-beam selection result
* Beam misalignment loss
* Angular-resolution comparison

---

### 08. OTA/MPAC Quiet-Zone Validation

This project studies OTA and MPAC chamber-validation concepts using simulation-based modeling of field uniformity, probe configuration, angular coverage, and quiet-zone behavior.

Key topics:

* Over-the-air validation
* Multi-probe anechoic chamber concept
* Quiet-zone field uniformity
* Probe antenna placement
* Spatial channel emulation
* Phase and amplitude variation

Typical outputs:

* Quiet-zone field map
* Probe geometry visualization
* Field-uniformity error
* Amplitude/phase variation plots
* Validation threshold comparison

---

### 09. NTN Doppler, Delay, and Link Validation

This project models non-terrestrial network link behavior by analyzing Doppler shift, propagation delay, link budget, and signal-quality degradation for satellite-based wireless communication.

Key topics:

* NTN propagation delay
* Doppler shift
* Satellite link budget
* Carrier-frequency offset
* Timing offset
* SNR degradation
* Compensation requirement analysis

Typical outputs:

* Doppler shift vs velocity
* Propagation delay vs altitude
* Received power vs distance
* SNR vs link distance
* NTN link-margin analysis

---

### 10. Monte Carlo Wireless Performance Analysis

This project uses Monte Carlo simulation to validate wireless-system performance under random channel, noise, fading, and interference conditions.

Key topics:

* Monte Carlo simulation
* BER estimation
* Outage probability
* Random channel realization
* Noise variation
* Interference modeling
* Statistical confidence

Typical outputs:

* BER vs SNR
* Outage probability vs threshold
* Histogram of received SINR
* Performance confidence interval
* Repeated-trial validation results

---

## Simulation Methodology

Each project follows the same validation methodology:

1. Define the wireless-system problem.
2. Specify assumptions and input parameters.
3. Implement the mathematical model.
4. Run MATLAB and/or Python simulations.
5. Generate plots and numerical results.
6. Compare performance against expected behavior.
7. Explain the engineering interpretation.
8. Document limitations and possible improvements.

---

## Tools and Languages

The repository uses:

* MATLAB for signal-processing simulation, RF/PHY modeling, algorithm validation, and engineering plots
* Python for numerical simulation, automation, result comparison, and visualization
* NumPy for numerical computation
* SciPy for signal-processing and statistical functions
* Matplotlib for plotting
* Git/GitHub for version control and documentation

---

## Example Validation Metrics

The projects use different validation metrics depending on the topic:

| Area             | Example Metrics                                               |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Link budget      | Received power, path loss, SNR, link margin                   |
| Channel modeling | Channel gain, fading depth, outage probability                |
| RF impairment    | EVM, ACLR, image rejection ratio                              |
| PA/DPD           | AM-AM, AM-PM, spectral regrowth, linearization gain           |
| Beamforming      | Beam gain, selected beam index, misalignment loss             |
| OTA/MPAC         | Quiet-zone amplitude error, phase variation, field uniformity |
| NTN              | Doppler shift, delay, link margin, CFO impact                 |
| Monte Carlo      | BER, outage probability, SINR distribution                    |

---

## Main Technical Objective

The main objective of this repository is to show simulation-based wireless engineering capability across RF, PHY, and system-level validation. The projects are designed to connect mathematical modeling, implementation, visualization, and engineering interpretation.

This repository is especially relevant to roles such as:

* Wireless System Engineer
* RF System Engineer
* RF/PHY Algorithm Engineer
* 5G/6G Research Engineer
* OTA Systems Engineer
* RF Validation Engineer
* PA/DPD Engineer
* NTN/Satellite Wireless Systems Engineer

